.TH "primaryRestore" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
primaryRestore \- restore primary nodes of replica groups based on saved
information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]SdbDC.primaryRestore(<planobjOrFile>, [option])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDC
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to restore primary nodes of replica groups based on the
information saved by primarySave().
It accepts the BSON object returned by primarySave, a plain JSON object, or a
file path containing the saved result.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
planobjOrFile ( \f[I]object | BSONObj | string, required\f[] )
.PP
Specify the primary node restore plan.
The following types are supported:
.IP \[bu] 2
object / BSONObj: The result object returned by primarySave(), which must
contain a Detail array
.IP \[bu] 2
string: The file path where primarySave() saved the result.
The function will read and parse the file content as a JSON object
.PP
option ( \f[I]object, optional\f[] )
.PP
Specify filtering conditions for the data groups to restore, as well as
additional reelect parameters through the parameter "option":
.IP \[bu] 2
HostName ( \f[I]string\f[] ): Filter by hostname, only restore data groups whose
PrimaryNode hostname matches
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]HostName: "sdbserver"\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Domain ( \f[I]string | array\f[] ): Filter by domain, only restore data groups
belonging to the specified domain(s).
A single domain name or an array of domain names can be specified
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]Domain: "mydomain"\f[] or
\f[C]Domain: ["domain1", "domain2"]\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Seconds ( \f[I]number\f[] ): Reelect timeout, default is 30, in seconds
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]Seconds: 60\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Level ( \f[I]number\f[] ): Reelect wait level, value range: [1, 3], default is 3
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
1: Wait for the current write operation to finish and block subsequent write
operations
.IP \[bu] 2
2: Wait for write cursors (LOB operations) to finish
.IP \[bu] 2
3: Wait for transactions to finish
.PP
Format: \f[C]Level: 3\f[]
.RE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
The planobjOrFile must contain a valid Detail array, and each element must
include GroupName and PrimaryNode fields.
.IP \[bu] 2
The PrimaryNode format is hostname:svcname.
The function will parse the HostName and ServiceName for the reelect operation.
.IP \[bu] 2
If the GroupName or PrimaryNode of an entry in Detail is missing, that entry
will be skipped.
.IP \[bu] 2
HostName filtering matches against the hostname in PrimaryNode; Domain filtering
matches against the domain the data group belongs to.
.RE
